PSR J2317+1439 has a fairly typical orbital period of 2.459 days and a very circular orbit with an eccentricity of 2.200e-06. It is a moderate pulsar with a 1400 MHz flux density of 4.0 mJy. This pulsar has a low-mass companion with a minimum mass of 0.172 solar masses.

It has a typical slow pulsar-like magnetic field strength of 1.24e+12 G. It was discovered in 1978 as part of the Green Bank Northern Hemisphere survey. It is a weak pulsar with a 1400 MHz flux density of 0.9 mJy. This pulsar appears to be solitary.
